Class Animal

  • java.lang.Object
    • PetStoreAPI.Animal
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Feedable, Sellable, Stockable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Bird, Fish, Mammal, Reptile
    public abstract class Animal
extends java.lang.Object
implements Stockable, Sellable, Feedable
    This class is the superclass for classes Bird, Fish, Mammal, and Reptile and implements the interfaces Stockable, Sellable, and Feedable.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Animal

        public Animal​(java.lang.String species,
              double itemValue,
              int quantity,
              Animal.Sex sex,
              int age,
              java.lang.String color,
              java.lang.String idMarks,
              java.lang.String image,
              boolean beenFed,
              java.lang.String comments)
        Parameters:
        species - name of species
        itemValue - dollar amount of item > 0.00
        quantity - amount of items to be changed, - or +
        sex - Animal.Sex.M, Animal.Sex.F, Animal.Sex.U (Unknown)
        age - > 0
        color - primary color of animal. secondary colors listed in comments.
        idMarks - documents unique marks on animal (scars, microchips, etc.). if none, type "none".
        image - picture of animal. if none, type "none".
        beenFed - true or false
        comments - any other documentation to enter. if none, type "none".
        Since:
        6/29/22
